  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Bohol</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At 8:12am on October 15th, 2013, a 7.2 magnitude earthquake shook the Visayan region of the Philippines. Initial reports were focused on numerous historical churches that were severely damaged. We now know that more than 12,000 homes have been totally destroyed and more than 34,000 have been partially damaged. The Philippines sits in the Ring of Fire, but the area around Bohol and Cebu are not accustomed to earthquakes. Residents are traumatized due to the earthquake and subsequent aftershocks.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Displaced Earthquake Survivors</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Program Details:

Project Bohol will initially be focused on a program called &#x201C;Safe Houses, Save Lives&#x201C; The earthquake has created thousands of extremely dangerous structures. What used to be a family home is now a precarious building that has its owners fearful to enter. AHV will be SAFE-ING these homes by carefully  bringing it down to the ground. In the process and after completion of the SAFE-ING as much of the construction materials as possible will be collected for re-use, re-purposing, recycling. This phase is referred to as deconstruction. Safety is paramount in this process. Some days will be more productive than others so we ask for your patience, but the goals are be safe and salvage as many materials as possible.</narrative>
  </description>
